{
  "0": "As we discuss exit options, note that Microsoft, Salesforce, and Zoom have each completed multi‑billion‑dollar acquisitions in the remote‑collaboration space, signaling strategic interest. Our product aligns well with their ecosystem goals.\n\nLooking ahead, we aim to grow ARR to $50 M by Year 3, which will position us for a robust IPO preparation phase in Year 4—engaging top banks and starting a roadshow. By Year 5 we target a $200 M market‑cap IPO on NASDAQ. This dual‑track approach gives us flexibility to maximize shareholder value."
}

[
  {
    "question": "Why target Microsoft, Salesforce, and Zoom as acquisition candidates?",
    "answer": "All three have demonstrated recent strategic acquisitions of remote‑collaboration tools (Miro, Airtable, Figma). Our AI‑driven platform complements their product suites and offers cross‑selling opportunities."
  },
  {
    "question": "What valuation assumptions underpin the $200 M IPO target?",
    "answer": "Based on a 5× revenue multiple applied to $40 M ARR projected for Year 5, plus a premium for strategic assets and our AI technology."
  },
  {
    "question": "How will you de‑risk the IPO pathway?",
    "answer": "By hitting defined revenue milestones, securing an audit‑ready financial model by Year 3, and engaging reputable investment banks early in Year 4 to shape the offering."
  }
]
